<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Stop the "Transport balloon crash" event from ever being offered.

    "Transport balloon crash" is Medieval Fantasy Themed Relic Quests' reskin (letter + text) of the
    vanilla RefugeePodCrash incident: an injured/factionless person crash-lands and is offered as a
    quest (Accept/Reject) to rescue, recruit, capture, or harvest them. RefugeePodCrash is a Misc-
    category IncidentWorker_GiveQuest; zeroing its baseChance (its weight in the Misc pool) did NOT
    reliably stop it. Instead empty its targetTags: an incident whose targetTags is empty fails
    IncidentWorker.CanFireNow for any target, so no storyteller comp can ever select it - the same
    bulletproof disable used for the ground trade caravans.

    Edits the Core incident directly, so it's global - no storyteller offers it.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
        <xpath>Defs/IncidentDef[defName="RefugeePodCrash"]/targetTags</xpath>
        <value>
            <targetTags />
        </value>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
